prompt:
Add a new public function called Clamp to Calculator.calr that clamps a value between min and max. It takes i32 parameters min, max, and value. Returns i32. The result should be min if value < min, max if value > max, otherwise value. Use function ID f003.

Use this exact pattern:
§F{f003:Clamp:pub}
  §I{i32:min}
  §I{i32:max}
  §I{i32:value}
  §O{i32}
  §Q (<= min max)
  §S (>= result min)
  §S (<= result max)
  §R (? (< value min) min (? (> value max) max value))
§/F{f003}

The precondition ensures min <= max, and postconditions ensure result is within [min, max].
